{
  "message": "chore: move CASS planning, research, and runbook docs into docs/planning/ + fix README link\n\nTwenty-one markdown documents at the repo root were planning docs,\nresearch notes, work-stream reports, and runbooks. They have lasting\nvalue as a record of how decisions were made, but they don't belong\nat the repo root competing with README.md, AGENTS.md, etc.\n\nThe PLAN_*.md files are particularly notable \u2014 there are 8 of them,\nseveral with parallel __OPUS / __CODEX / __GPT companion versions\nwhere multiple models were asked to draft a plan independently and\nthe best parts were merged. Those are the kind of \"shows the thought\nprocess\" docs the user explicitly asked to preserve, but their\nroot-level placement makes the project look unfocused. Same for the\nmodes-of-reasoning analyses, the agent-friendliness audit, the toon\nintegration brief, etc.\n\nFiles moved:\n\n- 8 PLAN_*.md (advanced optimizations dual drafts, semantic+hybrid\n  search, analytics-in-cass dual drafts, gh-pages export, original\n  cass plan, port-install-scripts-to-rust)\n- MODES_OF_REASONING_REPORT_AND_ANALYSIS_OF_PROJECT.md\n- RESEARCH_FINDINGS.md\n- RUST_CLI_TOOLS_BEST_PRACTICES_GUIDE.md\n- SUGGESTED_IMPROVEMENTS_TO_CASS_BASED_ON_CMS.md\n- SYNC_STRATEGY.md\n- TOON_INTEGRATION_BRIEF.md\n- UPGRADE_LOG.md\n- RECOVERY_RUNBOOK.md\n- AGENT_FRIENDLINESS_REPORT.md, AGENT_INTRODUCTION.md\n- SEMANTIC_SEARCH_BEADS.md\n- CASS_INDEXING_HISTORICAL_BENCHMARK_RESULTS.md\n- TESTING.md (per-project test/review/quality protocol; not the\n  language-test config which lives in Cargo.toml + tests/)\n\nReference fix: README.md\u00a72806 linked to TESTING.md by bare filename;\nupdated to docs/planning/TESTING.md so the link still resolves once\nthe move lands.\n\nThe docs/reference/ cluster moved separately in the prior commit\nbecause those four files cross-link each other and had to move as a\nunit.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>",
